  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Responding to Water Crisis in Al Qarna District in Basra</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through this project, IOM contributes to the recovery of Al Qarna district in Basra governorate (Iraq) by responding to the urgent needs caused by the water crisis and strengthening the resilience of the community towards water scarcity. IOM works to rehabilitate the water treatment plant seeking to drastically improve the access to clean water for about 100,000 people living in the Al Qarna district. In addition, IOM works to ensure the sustainability of the action through setting up and training a community-based management team for the effective and sustainable maintenance of the water treatment plant. Lastly, IOM aims to ensure the ownership of the project by training and liaising with the water authorities, in particular the Directorate of Water.</narrative>
  </description>
